---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const title = '@scope vs BEM';
const description = 'Compare CSS @scope and BEM for selector control, naming pressure, maintainability, and modern CSS architecture.';
---

<DocsLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <article>
        <p class="eyebrow">Comparison</p>
        <h1>@scope vs BEM</h1>

        <p>
            BEM solves accidental styling collisions with naming conventions.
            @scope solves many of the same problems with native browser behaviour.
        </p>

        <p>
            One asks developers to be disciplined. The other asks the platform
            to help. Both matter.
        </p>

        <h2>Main differences</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>BEM uses longer class names for safety</li>
            <li>@scope uses selector boundaries for safety</li>
            <li>BEM is convention-driven</li>
            <li>@scope is platform-native behaviour</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Recommended reading</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/writing/articles/css-scope-and-lscss/">@scope and LSCSS</a></li>
            <li><a href="/learn/comparisons/bem-vs-lscss/">BEM vs LSCSS</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/modern-css/">Modern CSS</a></li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</DocsLayout>
